also receive a bundle of rad SlideDeck skins. Rest assured, we’ve heard the community’s feedback loud and clear. The most common request we receive is “more vertical skins!” Which is why we’re dishing out not just one but two awesome vertical slide skins that can be customized to fit your website.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Reason #1 &#8211;  Vertical Feature Content (WordPress only):</strong><br\n/> This ultra minimal Smart SlideDeck skin allows users to fill the entire slide with the content of their choosing. Be it an image or a text/image combination, the unobtrusive dot navigation provides ample flexibility while navigating users quickly through the deck. Additionally, users can navigate by simply scrolling their mouse wheel up or down.</p><div\nclass=\"slidedeck_frame skin-vertical-dark\"><dl\nid=\"SlideDeck_750_8338\" class=\"slidedeck slidedeck_8338\" style=\"width:100%;height:300px\"><dt>Vertical Smart Slide 1</dt><dd><dl\nclass=\"slidesVertical\"><dt>Climbing Wall, Singa…</dt><dd><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-container\"><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-content\"><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-title\"><a\nhref=\"http://feeds.nationalgeographic.com/~r/ng/photography/photo-of-the-day/~3/RLx1EDpvOvA/\">Climbing Wall, Singapore</a></div><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-timesince\">Posted 5 hours ago</div><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-excerpt\"><p>Father and sons on rock Climbing at Singapore Air force open housing.</p></div><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-permalink\"><a\nhref=\"http://feeds.nationalgeographic.com/~r/ng/photography/photo-of-the-day/~3/RLx1EDpvOvA/\">Read More</a></div></div><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-image\"><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-image-child\"><a\nhref=\"http://feeds.nationalgeographic.com/~r/ng/photography/photo-of-the-day/~3/RLx1EDpvOvA/\"><img\nsrc=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-content/photos/000/396/cache/39674_360x270.jpg\" alt=\"Climbing Wall, Singapore\" /></a></div></div></div></dd><dt>Alpine Climbers, Mid…</dt><dd><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-container\"><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-content\"><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-title\"><a\nhref=\"http://feeds.nationalgeographic.com/~r/ng/photography/photo-of-the-day/~3/AiVbQrKnxyw/\">Alpine Climbers, Midi-Plan Traverse, France</a></div><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-timesince\">Posted 1 day ago</div><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-excerpt\"><p>Climbers moving along the ridge on the Classic alpine route \"The midi plan Traverse</p></div><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-permalink\"><a\nhref=\"http://feeds.nationalgeographic.com/~r/ng/photography/photo-of-the-day/~3/AiVbQrKnxyw/\">Read More</a></div></div><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-image\"><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-image-child\"><a\nhref=\"http://feeds.nationalgeographic.com/~r/ng/photography/photo-of-the-day/~3/AiVbQrKnxyw/\"><img\nsrc=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-content/photos/000/396/cache/39673_360x270.jpg\" alt=\"Alpine Climbers, Midi-Plan Traverse, France\" /></a></div></div></div></dd><dt>Girl on Swing, Bangl…</dt><dd><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-container\"><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-content\"><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-title\"><a\nhref=\"http://feeds.nationalgeographic.com/~r/ng/photography/photo-of-the-day/~3/amfj-cHu1co/\">Girl on Swing, Bangladesh</a></div><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-timesince\">Posted 2 days ago</div><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-excerpt\"><p>Taken from behind of Charukola, University of Dhaka. Kids were really enjoying the Nagor Dola.</p></div><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-permalink\"><a\nhref=\"http://feeds.nationalgeographic.com/~r/ng/photography/photo-of-the-day/~3/amfj-cHu1co/\">Read More</a></div></div><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-image\"><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-image-child\"><a\nhref=\"http://feeds.nationalgeographic.com/~r/ng/photography/photo-of-the-day/~3/amfj-cHu1co/\"><img\nsrc=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-content/photos/000/396/cache/39679_360x270.jpg\" alt=\"Girl on Swing, Bangladesh\" /></a></div></div></div></dd><dt>Sunset, Fort Myers B…</dt><dd><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-container\"><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-content\"><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-title\"><a\nhref=\"http://feeds.nationalgeographic.com/~r/ng/photography/photo-of-the-day/~3/KdAblQHR5YU/\">Sunset, Fort Myers Beach, Florida</a></div><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-timesince\">Posted 3 days ago</div><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-excerpt\"><p>Fort Myers Beach, Florida. USA. May 3rd 2011.The Sun looked huge. People would gather on the pier each night to watch it set.</p></div><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-permalink\"><a\nhref=\"http://feeds.nationalgeographic.com/~r/ng/photography/photo-of-the-day/~3/KdAblQHR5YU/\">Read More</a></div></div><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-image\"><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-image-child\"><a\nhref=\"http://feeds.nationalgeographic.com/~r/ng/photography/photo-of-the-day/~3/KdAblQHR5YU/\"><img\nsrc=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-content/photos/000/396/cache/39677_360x270.jpg\" alt=\"Sunset, Fort Myers Beach, Florida\" /></a></div></div></div></dd><dt>Middle Atlas Mountai…</dt><dd><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-container\"><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-content\"><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-title\"><a\nhref=\"http://feeds.nationalgeographic.com/~r/ng/photography/photo-of-the-day/~3/UJe8mNvEw4w/\">Middle Atlas Mountains, Morocco</a></div><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-timesince\">Posted 4 days ago</div><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-excerpt\"><p>The road in the mountains of the Middle Atlas, Morocco. I have done the African stage along the west coast of part of the world tour on a motorcycle.</p></div><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-permalink\"><a\nhref=\"http://feeds.nationalgeographic.com/~r/ng/photography/photo-of-the-day/~3/UJe8mNvEw4w/\">Read More</a></div></div><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-image\"><div\nclass=\"sd-node sd-node-image-child\"><a\nhref=\"http://feeds.nationalgeographic.com/~r/ng/photography/photo-of-the-day/~3/UJe8mNvEw4w/\"><img\nsrc=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-content/photos/000/400/cache/40052_360x270.jpg\" alt=\"Middle Atlas Mountains, Morocco\" /></a></div></div></div></dd></dl></dd></dl></div><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Reason #2 &#8211; Vertical Product Tour:</strong><br\n/> Perfect for complex processes, the Stacked Skin is designed for users that need text-oriented navigation to detail each slide. What you lose in slide real estate you gain with a highly apparent and interactive interface. *Note: For this skin to render properly you must make a SlideDeck with only <em>one </em>horizontal skin and multiple vertical skins.</p><div\nclass=\"slidedeck_frame skin-stacked-nav\"><dl\nid=\"SlideDeck_982_8330\" class=\"slidedeck slidedeck_8330\" style=\"width:100%;height:300px\"><dt>Slide 1</dt><dd><dl\nclass=\'slidesVertical\'><dt>Double Peak Park</dt><dd><p><img\nstyle=\"float: right; margin: 0 0 10px 10px;\" title=\"Landscape\" src=\"http://assets-www-slidedeck-com.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/slide_01-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></p><h3 style=\"font-size: 14px;margin: 0 0 10px\">Double Peak Park</h3><p>Mauris gravida porta mauris nec suscipit. Aliquam suscipit pellentesque enim, quis accumsan felis faucibus in. Duis nulla ipsum, auctor vel varius at, accumsan sagittis massa. Vivamus laoreet mollis mattis. Vivamus sit amet magna quis tortor pharetra pellentesque. Ut dapibus convallis vestibulum. Vivamus varius nibh et sapien vehicula a euismod lacus ultricies.</p></dd><dt>Bon Bon Tree</dt><dd><p><img\nclass=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-8342\" style=\"float: left; margin: 0 10px 10px 0;\" title=\"Bon Bon Tree\" src=\"http://assets-www-slidedeck-com.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/slide_02-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></p><h3 style=\"font-size: 14px;margin: 0 0 10px\">Bon Bon Tree</h3><p>Pellentesque condimentum enim rutrum tellus laoreet sed vestibulum urna suscipit. Integer vestibulum auctor sagittis. In volutpat euismod dolor ac ullamcorper. Aenean rhoncus pretium nibh at fringilla. Ut dapibus convallis vestibulum. Vivamus varius nibh et sapien vehicula a euismod lacus ultricies. In hac habitasse platea dictumst.</p></dd><dt>RC Cars</dt><dd><p><img\nclass=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-8343\" style=\"float: right; margin: 0 0 10px 10px;\" title=\"RC Cars\" src=\"http://assets-www-slidedeck-com.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/slide_03-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></p><h3 style=\"font-size: 14px;margin: 0 0 10px\">RC Cars</h3><p>Sed in facilisis velit. In ornare fermentum ligula, sodales luctus odio aliquam quis. Curabitur rhoncus velit sed nisi lacinia eget venenatis diam sodales. Sed nibh nulla, mollis et luctus et, condimentum et risus. Nulla vitae leo nunc. Cras ultricies pellentesque sollicitudin. Vivamus pharetra nisi eu neque molestie facilisis.</p></dd><dt>At The Dog Park</dt><dd><p><img\nclass=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-8344\" style=\"float:left;margin: 0 10px 10px 0\" title=\"Nina\" src=\"http://assets-www-slidedeck-com.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/slide_04-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></p><h3 style=\"font-size:14px;margin: 0 0 10px\">At The Dog Park</h3><p> Praesent enim augue, lacinia at viverra et, tincidunt aliquet est. Ut volutpat ligula sed ipsum molestie quis porttitor lacus feugiat. Etiam eget purus sed urna pretium elementum vel sed ligula. Praesent eu venenatis leo. Etiam vel est sapien. Mauris ultrices turpis ac metus imperdiet vel varius risus pharetra. Pellentesque pharetra venenatis dignissim.</p></dd></dl></dd></dl></div><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Reason #3 &#8211; Super Simple Gallery:</strong><br\n/> You may already be familiar with this popular new addition. As a purely CSS built skin, this lightweight SlideDeck will elegantly coincide with your existing design. Quickly override the color properties of the background, arrow containers, arrows and highlight colors to show off a seamless SlideDeck design.</p><div\nclass=\"slidedeck_frame skin-super-simple\"><dl\nid=\"SlideDeck_173_8310\" class=\"slidedeck slidedeck_8310\" style=\"width:100%;height:300px\"><dt>Double Peak Park</dt><dd\nstyle=\"background:url(http://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/slide_011.jpg) center center !important;\"></dd><dt>Bon Bon Tree</dt><dd\nstyle=\"background:url(http://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/slide_021.jpg) center center !important;\"><div><p>&nbsp;</p></div><p>&nbsp;</p></dd><dt>RC Car Race</dt><dd\nstyle=\"background:url(http://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/slide_031.jpg) center center !important;\"><div><p>&nbsp;</p></div><p>&nbsp;</p></dd></dl></div><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Our collection of SlideDeck skins continues to grow, which is all the more reason to upgrade if you have yet to do so. As always, please let us know what you think of the latest skins. If you have an idea for a new skin design, submit your feedback to the SlideDeck <a\nhref=\"http://support.slidedeck.com/slidedeck/topics/new?query=New%20SlideDeck%20Skin%20Idea\" target=\"_blank\">knowledge base</a>.</p><p><strong>New users &#8211; you&#8217;ll receive the skins in the file you download.  Already have PRO?  PRO users, download the latest version of the SlideDeck PRO plugin for WordPress (1.4) to obtain the new skins.</strong></p><p><em>As a reminder, be sure to review the instructions found in the readme.txt file included with each custom skin.</em></p> <div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=FIRV9J1x7lM:CnNhBqdSIVo:yIl2AUoC8zA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?d=yIl2AUoC8zA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=FIRV9J1x7lM:CnNhBqdSIVo:gIN9vFwOqvQ\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?i=FIRV9J1x7lM:CnNhBqdSIVo:gIN9vFwOqvQ\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=FI