:1110:\"<p>By default, <strong>WordPress</strong> includes <strong>/category/</strong> in the URL of your website so that it looks like <a href=\"http://thisismyurl.com/category/tutorials\">http://thisismyurl.com/category/tutorials</a> but if you want to remove the /category/ from your URL, there&#8217;s a quick and easy way.</p>\n<p>First, open WordPress and navigate to your Settings &gt; Permalinks and change your Custom Structure to<em> /%post_id%/%postname%/</em></p>\n<p>Next, set your Category Base to <em>/</em> and your Tag Base to <em>/t/</em></p>\n<p>Now save your changes and when you access pages across your site they&#8217;ll appear without <em>/category/</em> appearing in the title.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/E2PAROEMzQ7LwH0r4KKunIQTBtA/0/da\"><img src=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/E2PAROEMzQ7LwH0r4KKunIQTBtA/0/di\" border=\"0\" ismap=\"true\"></img></a><br/>\n<a href=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/E2PAROEMzQ7LwH0r4KKunIQTBtA/1/da\"><img src=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/E2PAROEMzQ7LwH0r4KKunIQTBtA/1/di\" border=\"0\" ismap=\"true\"></img></a></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"http://thisismyurl.com/2011/10/26/remove-category-url-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"3\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateF