lled the key ingredient in Thatcherism. This was coupled with financial deregulation. Together, they (arguably) produced improvements in economic performance. In this lecture, Zhou Penghui analyzes how privatization and deregulation takes place and their pros and cons.'),(3550,2369,'description','When a private enterprise fails to achieve optimal social outcomes, an instinctive response is for the government to intervene. One of the easiest ways to do that is to simply have the government take over the company entirely. This strips the company of it\'s profit earning incentives which it concerned itself with in the free market, and replaces it with government ordained (and not necessarily profitable) objectives.\r\n\r\nHowever, is that necessarily the best option? Zhou Penghui will tell you more.'),(3556,1629,'description','If Toyota is producing too many cars in Japan, one of the simplest ways to solve that is to tell Toyota \"Hey stop producing so many cars\" and to order it to produce a certain number of cars instead.\r\n\r\nThis is exactly what quotas do to agents bearing externalities.'),(3350,1791,'videourl','http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KOrpSNp1vh0'),(3359,1602,'videourl','http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UhyzF4HlV8Q'),(3353,1610,'videourl','http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fyD2zBfFtQw'),(3356,1607,'videourl','http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J2qccVauzfw'),(3362,1795,'videourl','http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mUASK6wwL4I'),(3365,1799,'videourl','http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mTuby4Syi_8'),(3368,1797,'videourl','http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=937vvdo0IfA'),(3371,1605,'videourl','http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qKC_6evoCzI'),(3374,1223,'videourl','http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FXurceIstGU'),(3377,1227,'videourl','http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QiRzLFhETUc'),(3380,1225,'videourl','http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tN_rKNNRMCc'),(3383,1221,'videourl','http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vDNmixjtcIY'),(3386,1219,'videourl','http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=U-D_B6fx1Gc'),(3389,