-10 21:01:44','2011-09-10 13:01:44','',888,'http://openlectures.sg/wordpress/uncategorized/888-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(890,1,'2011-09-10 21:19:19','2011-09-10 13:19:19','','Post Selector','','publish','closed','closed','','post-selector','','','2011-09-11 00:23:02','2011-09-10 16:23:02','',0,'http://openlectures.sg/wordpress/?post_type=sidebar&#038;p=890',0,'sidebar','',0),(895,1,'2011-09-10 21:56:41','2011-09-10 13:56:41','<div class=\"container\">\r\n	<div class=\"row\">\r\n		<div class=\"two-thirds column alpha\">\r\n			<img src=\"/wp-content/themes/olresponsive/img/about-us-masthead.png\">\r\n		</div><!--2/3col-->\r\n		<div class=\"one-third column omega\">\r\n			<h2><span class=\"openlectures\"><b>open</b>lectures</span>\r\n				is a community initiative brought to you by the combined efforts of more than fifty staff and lecturers whose only remuneration is seeing their dreams turn into reality.\r\n			</h2>\r\n		</div><!--1/3col-->\r\n	</div><!--row-->\r\n	<div class=\"row remove-bottom\">\r\n		<div class=\"one-third column alpha\">\r\n			<h3 class=\"current\">Concept</h3>\r\n			<p>\r\n				What happens if we take the best of the best and ask them to teach us how they\'ve done it? We\'ll set up a camera, give them a marker, and throw them in front of a whiteboard. Then we\'ll take that footage and make it available to the world - for free.\r\n			</p>\r\n		</div><!--1/3col-->\r\n		<div class=\"one-third column\">\r\n			<h3 class=\"current\">Philosophy</h3>\r\n			<p>\r\n				Everyone at <span class=\"openlectures\"><b>open</b>lectures</span> shares two things in common: an intimate grasp of their subject matter, and a fervent passion for sharing their knowledge. Everyone works <i>pro bono</i>, after office hours, and on weekends. Everyone loves what they\'re doing.\r\n			</p>\r\n		</div><!--1/3col-->\r\n		<div class=\"one-third column omega\">\r\n			<h3 class=\"current\">Mission</h3>\r\n			<p>\r\n				There\'s a hundred other e-learning alternatives we can name. Schools use them as supplementary material. Us? We\'re more than supplements, we\'re replacements. Look for us if you miss a class, then go back and join up without a worry in the world.\r\n			</p>\r\n		</div><!--1/3col-->\r\n		<div class=\"two-thirds column alpha\">\r\n			<blockquote>\r\n				We\'ll look at what we have and ask ourselves if we can make it better. If the answer is yes, we throw it away and start again. Stuff doesn\'t go up until the answer is no.\r\n				<cite>\r\n					<b>Linan Qiu</b>, CEO and Founder of <span class=\"openlectures\"><b>open</b>lectures</span>\r\n				</cite>\r\n			</blockquote>\r\n		</div><!--2/3col-->\r\n		<div class=\"one-third column omega\">\r\n			<h3 class=\"current\">Quality</h3>\r\n			<p>\r\n				We\'ve got crazy dedication to quality. Our lectures are checked, peer-checked, then quality-checked. What makes us sure we\'re teaching the correct thing? We\'re just sharing what we\'ve learnt.\r\n			</p>\r\n		</div><!--1/3col-->\r\n	</div><!--row-->\r\n	<h2>The Grunts</h2>\r\n	<div class=\"row remove-bottom\">\r\n		<div class=\"four columns alpha\">\r\n			<h4>Linan Qiu</h4>\r\n			<h5 class=\"current\">Founder</h5>\r\n			<p>As Founder and CEO, Linan\'s job is to make irresistable offers and y\'know, run the company. A student at Columbia University, he toys with dubstep beats and Hammond organs when he isn\'t married to his work.</p>\r\n		</div><!--4col-->\r\n		<div class=\"four columns\">\r\n			<h4>Zhang Yitao</h4>\r\n			<h5 class=\"current\">Founder</h5>\r\n			<p>Yitao sells ice to the eskimos and charges them a delivery fee. He makes his home somewhere in-between Stanford University and Silicon Valley, where he acquires and applies his vast experience in entrepreneurship.</p>\r\n		</div><!--4col-->\r\n		<div class=\"four columns\">\r\n			<h4>Lim Mingjie Kenneth</h4>\r\n			<h5 class=\"current\">Information Technology</h5>\r\n			<p>Being CIO means Kenneth manages the running code riot that powers the <span class=\"openlectures\"><b>open</b>lectures</span> site. He is responsible for the myriad of \"ghetto\" techniques that deliver lectures from behind the scenes.</p>\r\n		</div><!--4col-->\r\n		<div class=\"four columns omega\">\r\n			<h4>Law Kang Jie</h4>\r\n			<h5 class=\"current\">Public Relations</h5>\r\n			<p>Kang Jie talks to everyone. When he\'s done with them, they normally fall irrevocably in love with what we do here. A man with a preference for all things creative, ask him about fashion when you meet him.</p>\r\n		</div><!--4col-->\r\n		<div class=\"four columns alpha\">\r\n			<h4>Tek Yong Jian</h4>\r\n			<h5 class=\"current\">Operations</h5>\r\n			<p>Yong Jian started out as the one-man video editing team. He goes over every minute of footage just to ensure that sound and video look professional. He does not own a computer.</p>\r\n		</div><!--4col-->\r\n		<div class=\"four columns\">\r\n			<h4>Lee Cheng Feng Gary</h4>\r\n			<h5 class=\"current\">Academics</h5>\r\n			<p>As CAO, Gary commands our veritable formation of lecturers. He oversees curriculum planning, lecture content and anything else. He is currently single and available.</p>\r\n		</div><!--4col-->\r\n		<div class=\"eight columns omega\">\r\n			<blockquote>\r\n				We are crazy people. But it takes crazy people to do crazy things. And crazy things are good things.\r\n				<cite>\r\n					<b>Lim Mingjie Kenneth</b>, CIO of <span class=\"openlectures\"><b>open</b>lectures</span>\r\n				</cite>\r\n			</blockquote>\r\n		</div><!--8col-->\r\n	</div><!--row-->\r\n	<p>It was written on an ancient scroll that we grow by accepting talent - not rejecting it. If you\'ve got something for us, head over to the <a href=\"/staff-lounge\">Staff Lounge</a>. We\'ll have something for you. If you just want to chat, head over there anyway.</p>\r\n	<h2>Why Bother?</h2>\r\n	<div class=\"row remove-bottom\">\r\n		<div class=\"eight columns alpha\">\r\n			<h4><span class=\"openlectures\"><b>open</b>lectures</span> aims to build a platform for students to learn in a manner complementary to their schooling.<br/> We want to return the power of learning to individuals, instead of leaving it to a system that is not tailored to suit everyone’s needs.</h4>\r\n			<br/>\r\n			<p>We believe that education should not be limited by wealth or the ability to afford it. Knowledge should not be traded. It should be accessible to everyone who wants to learn. We also believe that education should be based on learning, not studying; sharing, not teaching. Having benefited from our education, we are motivated to give back by sharing our experience and expertise with students who wants to better themselves by learning. Everyone at <span class=\"openlectures\"><b>open</b>lectures</span> contributes based on that principle. Think of it as getting the best tutors you could possibly find, anytime, anywhere and at zero cost.</p>\r\n		</div><!--8col-->	\r\n		<div class=\"eight columns omega alignright\">\r\n			<img src=\"\">\r\n		</div><!--8col-->	\r\n	</div><!--row-->\r\n	<h2>The Production Line</h2>\r\n	<p>At least six hours of work goes into a single lecture. Here\'s what happens when we roll up our sleeves and get down to work.</p>\r\n	<div class=\"row\">\r\n		<div class=\"four columns alpha\">\r\n			<img src=\"/wp-content/themes/olresponsive/img/Forming.png\"></div><!--4col-->	\r\n		<div class=\"four columns\">\r\n			<img src=\"/wp-content/themes/olresponsive/img/Storming.png\"></div><!--4col-->	\r\n		<div class=\"four columns\">\r\n			<img src=\"/wp-content/themes/olresponsive/img/Norming.png\"></div><!--4col-->	\r\n		<div class=\"four columns omega\">\r\n			<img src=\"/wp-content/themes/olresponsive/img/Performing.png\"></div><!--4col-->	\r\n		<div class=\"four columns alpha\">\r\n			<h4 class=\"aligncenter\">Forming</h4>\r\n			<p>In the first stage of planning, we gather a team of students with tremendous exposure and experience in the subject matter. We sit down for coffee. Many rounds of coffee. Our lecturers get comfortable saying no to each other.</p>\r\n		</div><!--4col-->	\r\n		<div class=\"four columns\">\r\n			<h4 class=\"aligncenter\">Storming</h4>\r\n			<p>It all starts with an outline. What goes in, what stays out, what\'s unclear. Everyone looks at that outline, then it\'s what\'s good, and what sucks. Fifteen to twenty revisions later, we have a list of lectures.</p>\r\n		</div><!--4col-->	\r\n		<div class=\"four columns\">\r\n			<h4 class=\"aligncenter\">Norming</h4>\r\n			<p>Allocation time. Our lecturers know what they know best, so we lay everything out <i>a la mode</i> buffet. Every lecture belongs to someone. From there, we work out the preparation material. More coffee.</p>\r\n		</div><!--4col-->	\r\n		<div class=\"four columns omega\">\r\n			<h4 class=\"aligncenter\">Performing</h4>\r\n			<p>We go down to headquarters at a top secret location. The on-site support team awaits. There\'s this big, scary camera they use to do the recording. The footage is edited and corrected, then sent for quality checks.</p>\r\n		</div><!--4col-->	\r\n	</div><!--row-->	\r\n</div><!--container-->','About Us','','publish','closed','closed','','about-us','','','2012-01-28 22:57:36','2012-01-28 14:57:36','',0,'http://openlectures.sg/wordpress/?page_id=895',0,'page','',0),(1888,1,'2011-09-20 20:38:36','2011-09-20 12:38:36','','Allocative Efficiency: Part 1','','inherit','open','open','','1190-revision-2','','','2011-09-20 20:38:36','2011-09-20 12:38:36','',1190,'http://openlectures.sg/uncategorized/1190-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(3113,1,'2011-12-30 00:13:42','2011-12-29 16:13:42','','Summary of Formula of Elasticities','','inherit','open','open','','1122-revision-2','','','2011-12-30 00:13:42','2011-12-29 16:13:42','',1122,'http://openlectures.sg/uncategorized/1122-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(2783,29,'2011-12-11 18:34:09','2011-12-11 10:34:09','','Shifts in the Demand Curve','','inherit','open','open','','875-revision-3','','','2011-12-11 18:34:09','2011-12-11 10:34:09','',875,'