ices for education</h3>\r\nBaumol’s cost disease is a term used to describe the phenomenon where salaries rise in jobs that experience no increase in productivity. Coined by William Baumol, an influential American economist, the term aptly describes the job of a tuition teacher. Ten years ago, one tuition teacher taught at most a few students. The tuition teacher today does the same but for higher prices.\r\n\r\nWe don’t think that should be the way things work nor the way you as a parent should allocate your money. There must be better ways for your child to revise certain topics, clarify some misconceptions and go through reruns of lectures without invoking costly tuition expenses.\r\n\r\nThis is why we created Open Lectures. Through us, your child can gain access to top quality lectures entirely free of charge. The lectures can be tuned to his own pace with a simple pause button. There is no penalty for missing lessons at Open Lectures, simply because there is no such thing as missing lessons. Our class is always open.\r\n\r\nIn fact, it is even open to you. Listen to the lessons your child goes through and experience Open Lectures for yourself. Quality control does not get better than this.\r\n\r\nEncourage your child to try Open Lectures as an alternative way to supplement your child’s formal education. We might just be the resource he is looking for.','Parents','','draft','open','closed','','parents','','','2011-10-29 20:20:17','2011-10-29 12:20:17','',0,'http://openlectures.sg/wordpress/?page_id=962',0,'page','',0),(964,1,'2011-09-15 21:46:51','2011-09-15 13:46:51','<h3>No one should pay exorbitant prices for education</h3>\nBaumol’s cost disease is a term used to describe the phenomenon where salaries rise in jobs that experience no increase in productivity. Coined by William Baumol, an influential American economist, the term aptly describes the job of a tuition teacher. Ten years ago, one tuition teacher taught at most a few students. The tuition teacher t