olute increase that we are concerned with in elasticity analysis), the quantity demanded will decrease by 5%. Revenue will increase because\n\nNew revenue = 1.5 x Original Price x 0.95 x Original Quantity = 1.425 x Original Revenue\n\nThe reverse applies for a good with a price elastic demand. Try it!','Application of Price Elasticity of Demand: Price Setting','','inherit','open','open','','1116-autosave','','','2011-12-11 19:09:19','2011-12-11 11:09:19','',1116,'http://openlectures.sg/uncategorized/1116-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(2761,29,'2011-12-11 19:09:33','2011-12-11 11:09:33','','Determinants of Price Elasticity of Supply','','inherit','open','open','','1114-revision','','','2011-12-11 19:09:33','2011-12-11 11:09:33','',1114,'http://openlectures.sg/uncategorized/1114-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(1120,15,'2011-09-18 16:50:33','2011-09-18 08:50:33','','Application of Cross Elasticity of Demand and Income Elasticity of Demand','','draft','open','open','','application-of-cross-elasticity-of-demand-and-income-elasticity-of-demand','','','2012-01-23 10:07:42','2012-01-23 02:07:42','',0,'http://openlectures.sg/?p=1120',15,'post','',0),(3116,1,'2011-12-30 00:13:43','2011-12-29 16:13:43','','Application of Price Elasticity of Demand: Price Setting','','inherit','open','open','','1116-revision-2','','','2011-12-30 00:13:43','2011-12-29 16:13:43','',1116,'http://openlectures.sg/uncategorized/1116-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(3117,1,'2011-12-30 00:13:43','2011-12-29 16:13:43','','Determinants of Price Elasticity of Supply','','inherit','open','open','','1114-revision-2','','','2011-12-30 00:13:43','2011-12-29 16:13:43','',1114,'http://openlectures.sg/uncategorized/1114-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(3277,1,'2012-01-23 22:50:31','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2012-01-23 22:50:31','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://openlectures.sg/?p=3277',0,'post','',0),(3284,1,'2012-01-23 23:07:41','2012-01-23 15:07:41','','[01